subject: Add ability to initiate and view resource dumps
commitMessage:
Add ability to initiate and view resource dumps

- An option will be added to initiate resource dump
- The API used to create resource dump is: /redfish/v1/Systems/system/LogServices/Dump/Actions/LogService.CollectDiagnosticData
- This patchset also adds the ability to view hostboot dumps since resource and hostboot dumps are returned
  by /redfish/v1/Systems/system/LogServices/Dump/Entries.

- While initiating resource dumps:
  a) Resource selector and resource password is hardcoded in API to
     accommodate the current state of the backend and UI will update
     with backend changes.
  b) For CE login, the user cannot view the password field since service login is not enabled.

Signed-off-by: Sukanya Pandey <sukapan1@in.ibm.com>
Change-Id: I1b293fbdbcc718ef6768cc0f2dd350e2fc3da103

Please don't hardcode URIs like this.  It disobeys the redfish specification, which requires walking the hypermedia API.

Done for '/redfish/v1/Managers/bmc/LogServices/Dump/Entries'.
For '/redfish/v1/Systems/system/LogServices/Dump/Entries' URL hypermedia @odata.id cannot be used because API structure is not appropriate and we doesn't know under 'Members' array where the object will present

We need to verify if System Dumps will ever show here. System dumps are large disruptive dumps that are offloaded and I don't expect will rarely if ever be listed in this table. There was some discussion that they may be listed if there was an issue offloading, but I am not sure we need this filter option. 

Since this story has been waiting for such a long time, I think we need to make a story to investigate, rather than delaying this story.

A couple of things. Since this is tested and about to receive a +2, but I have some concerns about the backend and am waiting for feedback from Dhruv to determine if these values are required and if they are, how that impacts the availability of this dump. If password and resource selector are required, this is a service login only function and we will need to discuss if this should be a downstream change only.

If not, we need to know the expectation for formatting the string to pass in the payload.
